0. Modify ntp file for syncing 
1. Create ssh keys so machines can scp information
2. ON PROD my.cnf with the following under [mysqld]
    server-id = 1
    binlog-do-db=tecmint
    relay-log = /var/lib/mysql/mysql-relay-bin
    relay-log-index = /var/lib/mysql/mysql-relay-bin.index
    log-error = /var/lib/mysql/mysql.err
    master-info-file = /var/lib/mysql/mysql-master.info
    relay-log-info-file = /var/lib/mysql/mysql-relay-log.info
    log-bin = /var/lib/mysql/mysql-bin
3.  restart mysqld service
4.  GRANT REPLICATION SLAVE ON *.* TO 'hudl'@'%' IDENTIFIED BY 'demo';
    FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
    FLUSH TABLES WITH READ LOCK;
    SHOW MASTER STATUS;

    **Gather mysql-bin.#### and Position

5. mysqldump -u root -p --all-databases --master-data > /root/dbdump.db
   UNLOCK TABLES;

6. scp /root/dbdump.db root@192.168.1.2:/root/

SLAVE

7. Edit my.cnf under [mysql]:
    server-id = 2
    master-host=192.168.1.1
    master-connect-retry=60
    master-user=slave_user
    master-password=yourpassword
    replicate-do-db=tecmint
    relay-log = /var/lib/mysql/mysql-relay-bin
    relay-log-index = /var/lib/mysql/mysql-relay-bin.index
    log-error = /var/lib/mysql/mysql.err
    master-info-file = /var/lib/mysql/mysql-master.info
    relay-log-info-file = /var/lib/mysql/mysql-relay-log.info
    log-bin = /var/lib/mysql/mysql-bin

8. mysql -u root -p < /root/dbdump.db
9. service mysqld restart
10. Login to mysql and run:
    slave stop;
    CHANGE MASTER TO MASTER_HOST='192.168.50.10', MASTER_USER='hudl', MASTER_PASSWORD='demo', MASTER_LOG_FILE='mysql-bin.####', MASTER_LOG_POS=###;
    slave start;
    show slave status\G


MASTER

11. create new database entry

SLAVE

12. verify new database entry
    use User_Profiles;
    select * from profiles;

